ic Swerve Library"></template></span> should be dividing by the gear ratio instead of multiplying.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-02-14T02:23:52.586Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":140,"readers_count":139,"score":53.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":491642,"topic_slug":"yagsl-calculates-our-max-ang-velocity-to-be-12000rad-s","display_username":"Christopher149","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":58460,"username":"andriibessarab","name":"Andrii Bessarab","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/andriibessarab/{size}/258546_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":14984,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"FRC857 lead mentor / FTC10723+13284+15270 lead mentor"},"post_url":"/t/yagsl-calculates-our-max-ang-velocity-to-be-12000rad-s/491642/4","custom_user_title":"FRC857 lead mentor / FTC10723+13284+15270 lead mentor","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3526703,"name":"Andrii Bessarab","username":"andriibessarab","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/andriibessarab/{size}/258546_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-14T02:35:21.460Z","cooked":"<p>That would make more sence (~4 rot/sec sounds more realistic).</p>
<p>Also, now that I think about it, perhaps, I am supposed to use<code> getMaximumChassisAngularVelocity()</code> instead? As the max angular speed of the robot as the whole would not neccessarily be the max angular speed of individual azimuth motors?</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-02-14T02:38:20.573Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":128,"readers_count":127,"score":35.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":491642,"topic_slug":"yagsl-calculates-our-max-ang-velocity-to-be-12000rad-s","display_username":"Andrii Bessarab","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":14984,"username":"Christopher149","name":"Christopher149","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/838e76/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":58460,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"4951 Alumni"},"post_url":"/t/yagsl-calculates-our-max-ang-velocity-to-be-12000rad-s/491642/5","custom_user_title":"4951 Alumni","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3526803,"name":"","username":"nstrike","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/nstrike/{size}/167038_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-14T05:20:16.654Z","cooked":"<p>Yeah i probably should. Might be my bad. Could you divide it and test to see if its too small? I really dont want teams to have a big change this year if i do 